[ctns_make id='gen_linear_func_general_form_linear_function']

  [ctns_front style='']
General Form<br/>Linear Function
  [/ctns_front]  

  [ctns_back style='width:80%;font-size:85%;']
The <strong>General Form</strong> of a linear function is given by the equation, $|Ax+By=C,|$ for all $$x,y \in \mathbb{R}$$ and where $$A$$, $$B$$, and $$C$$ are constants.
  [/ctns_back]  

  [ctns_frontspeak]
General Form - - - Linear Function
  [/ctns_frontspeak]  

  [ctns_backspeak]
The general form of a linear function is given by the equation -- Ei times X -- plus -- Bee times Y equal to C -- for all real numbers -- x and y -- where - A - B - and C - are constants.
  [/ctns_backspeak]  

[/ctns_make]
